[2026-07-04T09:45:00] TASK 1B — PIVOT (post-review fix)
Adversarial review (logs/adversarial-generalist.build.log, "TASK 1B
REVIEW") found a real credential-leak bug in `pubmed.py`'s `_get`:
`response.raise_for_status()` sat outside the `try/except httpx.HTTPError`
block, so any non-429/non-5xx 4xx response (400 malformed query, 403 bad
API key, etc.) raised an uncaught `httpx.HTTPStatusError` whose `str()`
embeds the full request URL — and `_common_params()` puts `email`/
`api_key` directly in the query string on every call, so that URL
contains NCBI_EMAIL/NCBI_API_KEY in plaintext. Since CONTRACTS.md
documents an eventual catch-all handler (Task 3D) that will very likely
log unhandled exceptions verbatim, this was a real path for credentials
to land in shared logs — confirmed correct, no test previously covered
any 4xx other than 429.
