[2026-07-04T03:10:00] TASK 1C — PIVOT (post-review fix)
Adversarial review (logs/adversarial-generalist.build.log, "TASK 1C
REVIEW") found a credential-leak bug at backend/app/auth/oauth.py:166
(same class as a bug just fixed in Task 1B's PubMed client):
`logger.exception("...missing userID: %r", tokens)` logged the raw
access-token response dict on the missing-`userID` error path. Per
requests-oauthlib's actual token-parsing behavior, `tokens` normally
contains the live, unencrypted `oauth_token`/`oauth_token_secret` bearer
credentials that §9.6 requires be Fernet-encrypted via
`app.models.crypto` before ever reaching storage — this log line wrote
usable plaintext credentials to server logs on a malformed response,
bypassing the encryption story entirely since this error path never
reaches the encryption call site. Fixed: now logs only
`sorted(tokens.keys())` (redacted metadata, no values) instead of the raw
dict via `%r`. Added
`test_complete_handshake_missing_userid_never_logs_raw_credentials` in
tests/test_oauth.py — feeds a response with realistic-looking
`oauth_token`/`oauth_token_secret` values and a missing `userID`, and
asserts via `caplog` that neither value appears anywhere in the captured
log text.
Worked: `pytest -q tests/test_oauth.py tests/test_zotero.py` => 17
passed (16 prior + 1 new). Full suite `pytest -q` => 119 passed, 2 failed
— both failures are in tests/test_pubmed_client.py (Task 1B's file, not
touched by this fix; appears to be a concurrent in-flight change on
1B's own credential-leak fix, outside this task's scope). `ruff check .`
=> all checks passed. `mypy app/` => success, no issues (21 source
files).
